For example, as of rc5, the vm operations class generated for the compute mgmt package (https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/blob/master/azure-mgmt-compute/azure/mgmt/compute/operations/virtual_machines_operations.py) has the following definition for the get method:

    def get(self, resource_group_name, vm_name, api_version="2016-03-30", expand=None, custom_headers=None, raw=False, **operation_config):

Since specifying an API version other than 2016-03-30 has the potential to break the client (the schema for responses is allowed to change between API versions), the api_version shouldn't be a parameter to the method. Instead, it should be a class level attribute or similar.

